```
Reason:
The `SAXReader` is instantiated without any configuration to disable DOCTYPE processing, which makes the application vulnerable to XML External Entity (XXE) attacks. This allows attackers to include external entities in the XML input, potentially leading to unauthorized access to sensitive data.

The code statements that fix the bug are:
```java
protected SAXReader createReader() throws DocumentException {
    final SAXReader reader = new SAXReader();
    reader.setFeature("http://apache.org/xml/features/disallow-doctype-decl", true);
}
```
Reason:
The `createReader` method initializes the `SAXReader` with a feature that disables DOCTYPE processing. This prevents the XML parser from processing external entities, thereby mitigating the XXE vulnerability.

